  <bodyText><![CDATA[<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Explore the hidden gems of Europe in comfort, style, and without breaking your stride. Our self-guided walking holidays are perfect for people who want to explore a destination at their own pace. Take your time to enjoy the great outdoors, and discover some of Europe’s most unspoiled corners.</span></p>
<p><img style="width: 100%; height: auto;" src="/media/13093748/easy-her0.png?width=169&amp;height=21" alt="easy walking holidays" data-udi="umb://media/d271ea268e76474799bc83698a2d69a5" /></p>
<h2>What to expect from our easy walking holidays</h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">We're passionate about walking holidays, and we want you to get the most out of yours. We offer easy walks through Europe's most beautiful destinations, where you can explore the local culture and make your own discoveries.</span></p>
<div class="g4">
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<h3>Free guided walks included in your holiday</h3>
<p><img style="width: 100%px; height: autopx;" src="/media/13093530/close-up-feet.png?width=0&amp;height=0" alt="" data-udi="umb://media/ada05f0bc8de4c3d84cb81a1965dba1d" /></p>
<ul>
<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">We offer free guided walks in select resorts, run by local experts who will help you make the most of your holiday.</span></li>
<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">We'll guide you through some of the best parts of each location with insider tips and tricks. </span></li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
<div class="g4">
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<h3>Our self-guided walking holidays offer total flexibility</h3>
<p><img style="width: 100%px; height: auto;" src="/media/13093531/close-up-walking.png?width=0&amp;height=0" alt="" data-udi="umb://media/6a1275fcf4c849cc870dc70996b0952e" /></p>
<ul>
<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">You'll be free to explore on your own terms. Whether you want to take a leisurely stroll or try something more strenuous.</span></li>
<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">You'll have the support of our resort representatives to offer advice and tips if you need it. </span></li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
<div class="g4">
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<h3>See more, do more and discover more</h3>
<p><img style="width: autopx; height: 100%;" src="/media/13080490/merano-tourist-board-image-8.jpg?width=500&amp;height=268.49642004773267" alt="" data-udi="umb://media/ddef516ea88a4726b9a4ac183045b915" /></p>
<ul>
<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">When you travel with us you'll experience a lot more than on a typical walking holiday. </span></li>
<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">We've chosen our European resorts for their culture and cuisine, as well as their endless activities and sights.</span></li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
<p> </p>
<h2>Discover our popular resorts for easy walking holidays</h2>
<p data-pm-slice="1 1 []">Explore Europe’s most beautiful walking destinations with us. Our easy walks are perfect for all abilities, and there’s something for everyone. Whether your focus is the stunning Italian Lakes or Austrian Mountains, there’s endless walking destinations available to explore - from the effortlessly scenic to off-the-beaten track adventures that offer even greater reward.</p>
<div class="g6">
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<h2>Seefeld, Austria</h2>
<p><img style="width: 100%; height: auto;" src="/media/13093749/austria-easy-walks.png?width=178&amp;height=21" alt="austria walking holiday" data-udi="umb://media/183b42bf0d2a4d7e954335a4adcf46bd" /></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">This small town is nestled in the mountains, close to a number of walks and trails. It has lots to offer families, with lots of low level walks and activities. Seefeld is also very well-connected by train, so it's easy to explore further on in the surrounding area.</span></p>
<p><strong>Seefeld walking highlights:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>The Lakes of Mittenwald</strong>: Mittenwald is a beautiful town in the Oberallgäu region of Bavaria, Germany. Close to Innsbruck, this walk takes you on an easy walk through the woods around Mittenwald with some great views along the way.</span></li>
<li><strong>Reitherjochalm Hut Walk</strong>:This walk starts at the bottom of the Rosshuette cable car. First you head to the end of the Hermannstal valley, where the Woldrichsteig track branches off to the right for a short ascent. The path heads slightly downhill, joining the track from the <span>Maximilianhütte</span> and then gently climbs to the Reitherjochalm. This is a great spot for refreshments and relaxing on deckchairs while enjoying some homemade classic Tyrolean food.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong><a data-udi="umb://document/21c1e3e8d6be4c0fbbf64e72cf57a152" href="/{localLink:umb://document/21c1e3e8d6be4c0fbbf64e72cf57a152}" title="Walking Holidays in Italy">Find out more about Seefeld &gt;&gt;</a></strong></p>
<p> </p>
<p> </p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="g6">
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<h2>Grindelwald, Switzerland</h2>
<p><img style="width: auto; height: 100%;" src="/media/13077738/grindelwald-first-sommer-bachalpsee.jpg?width=169&amp;height=21" alt="easy walking holidays" data-udi="umb://media/c5aedc63bc994f11bf95d957154c9e65" /></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Set at the foot of the impressive ‘North Face’ of the Eiger, Grindelwald is an ideal base from which to explore both sides of its dramatic valley. With easy access by rail, cable-car and gondola, there are many excellent walking trails in this region.</span></p>
<p><strong>Grindelwald walking highlights:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Bachalp Lake and back to First with optional Cliff Walk</strong>:<span style="font-weight: 400;"> The hike from First Mountain station to Lake Bachalp follows a gentle undulating and meandering path through flower filled meadows with stunning views of the surrounding peaks including the majestic Eiger and over to Kleine Scheidegg and Mannlichen. The path will wind its way past cow sheds, barns and farming chalets until you reach Bachalp lake.</span></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Mountain Panorama Trail – First over to Grosse Scheidegg</strong>: <span style="font-weight: 400;">Enjoy a walk through the mountains of Grindelwald. The views are spectacular! You can start this walk from top of First mountain and walk over to Grosse Scheidegg and then catch the yellow Grindelwald Bus back into the resort or do the other way round. Catch the bus up to Grosse Scheidegg then walk over to First and then catch the gondola back down to resort.</span></p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><strong><a data-udi="umb://document/0fe9200934b24cd49d20e1cea080f5da" href="/{localLink:umb://document/0fe9200934b24cd49d20e1cea080f5da}" title="Grindelwald">Find out more about Grindelwald&gt;&gt;</a></strong></p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="g6">
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<h2>Merano, Italy</h2>
<p><img style="width: 100%; height: auto;" src="/media/13080488/lm_mro_gen_h02.jpg?width=169&amp;height=21" alt="easy walking holidays" data-udi="umb://media/d9bb2945b30644cb8ab38d3656d14ed8" /></p>
<p>Merano is a beautiful spa town in South Tyrol, Italy, known for its stunning alpine scenery and excellent hiking and biking opportunities. Spend your day hiking in the morning and biking in the afternoon, then stroll into town for an aperitif and wonderful local cuisine in the evening.<span style="font-weight: 400;"></span></p>
<p><strong>Merano walking highlights:</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;"></span></p>
<ul>
<li><strong>The Tappeiner Trail</strong>: <span style="font-weight: 400;">The Tappeiner Trail is a lovely walk that can be enjoyed by anyone at any level of fitness. Located above Merano, it winds along the hillside of the Monte di Merano and offers spectacular views of the gentle streams and local flowers. There's even a little herb garden on the trail where you can see over 200 species of herbs!</span></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Sissi's Path:</strong> <span style="font-weight: 400;">Sissi's Path is a walk that's said to follow the footsteps of Empress Elisabeth of Austria. The route takes you through the town and out to her holiday residence, Trauttmansdorff Castle, before heading to Empress Elisabeth Park in Merano's center, where you'll find a statue of her. It's a scenic route with some great sights along the way.</span></p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><strong><a data-udi="umb://document/c5c478381e04431da3f69d8364215ae7" href="/{localLink:umb://document/c5c478381e04431da3f69d8364215ae7}" title="Merano">Find out more about Merano &gt;&gt;</a></strong></p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="g6">
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<h2>Chamonix, France</h2>
<p><img style="width: 100%; height: auto;" src="/media/13082473/fra_cha_twincntrs_walking.jpg?width=169&amp;height=21" alt="easy walking holidays" data-udi="umb://media/86c39a3edb714ac1862cfdaceb9443f2" /></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Chamonix is a fantastic place for beginners wishing to start walking, with a great variety of trails to try out. There are lots of things to do in resort, with our hotels ideally placed in the centre of the resort, close to shops, cafes, bars and restaurants. The huge choice of outdoor activities - rafting, parapenting, mountain biking, climbing, horse riding and summer tobogganing – makes Chamonix a fantastic all round choice for families looking for somewhere new to explore.</span></p>
<p><strong>Chamonix walking highlights:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>Lac des Gaillands:</strong> A lovely walk to the lakes, starting at the roundabout on the high street (A1 on the town map). Take either Route des Pecles or Avenue Ravanel le Rouge until you reach the lakes. Alternatively, you can take Promenade Marie Paradis on the other side of the river.</span></li>
<li><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>Petit Balcon Nord, Argentiere to Les Bois:</strong> You will be captured by the magical scenery of the French Alps as you pass through forests, cross the Arveyron and experience stunning views of glaciers. There's much to explore on this route! Love animals? You'll encounter lots of cows and goats grazing in the fields. </span></li>
</ul>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong><a data-udi="umb://document/2735e2389f7c411cb3061226ce7548d1" href="/{localLink:umb://document/2735e2389f7c411cb3061226ce7548d1}" title="Chamonix">Find out more about Chamonix&gt;&gt;</a></strong></span></p>
</div>
</div>
<p> </p>
